{"search_data": "Himachal PradeshHP Dev Bhoomi Darshan Yojana for Senior Citizens to Visit Holy Places (Dev Bhumi) Himachal Pradesh govt. starts HP Dev Bhoomi Darshan Yojana for senior citizens to enable them to visit holy places, govt. to provide 50% discount in bus fare to elderly people in age group of 70 to 80 years & free of cost travel of above 80 year people to visit dev bhumiHP Dev Bhoomi Darshan Yojana for Senior CitizensThe important features and highlights of Dev Bhumi Darshan Yojana are as follows:-The state govt. will provide relief in travel expenses to senior citizens to enable them to visit sacred places in the state.All the senior citizens between the age group of 70 to 80 years will get 50% discount in buses while travelling to dev bhumi.In addition to this, senior citizens who are 80 years or above in age will get full 100% discount in bus travel. They will not have to bear any expense while travelling to holy places under Dev Bhoomi Darshan Yojana.HP Dev Bhumi Darshan YojanaVarious other decisions were also taken in the cabinet meeting held on 24 September 2018. In Fire Department, govt. would fill 2 posts for station fire officers, 3 posts for driver-cum-pump operator, 20 firemen posts on contractual basis. In forest department, the state govt. has approved to fill 123 forest guards posts.A total number of 35 assistant professors / equivalent posts are approved for Dr. Y.S. Parmar University of Horticulture & Forestry. Honorarium for school teachers appointed by the School Management Committee is now increased by 20% per month and this amount is implemented w.e.f from 1 August 2018.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}